          "date": "2014-04-26 12:25:03.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-4945 mdc: resolve hash conflict with same hash offset",
        "message": "LU-4945 mdc: resolve hash conflict with same hash offset\n\nThe original way to resolve hash conflicts is to keep entry\npointer during iteration, but it needs to hold the ldlm lock,\notherwise entry(op_ent) might refer to some random entris.\n\nIt will use op_same_hash_offset to remember entry offset among\nthe same hash entries, so mdc_read_entry will tell which entry\nthe caller needs.\n\nSigned-off-by: wang di <di.wang@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I9d2c4daec534a32a539de5ab0f6ccb57065cb740\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
